Peter Dada, Akure The Ondo State Independent Electoral Commission on Wednesday said it was ready to conduct a free, fair and credible local government election. The commission had fixed April 18, 2020, for the chairmanship and councillorship elections across the 18 local government areas of the state. Addressing journalists at the ODIEC secretariat in Akure, the Chairman of the commission, Prof. Yomi Dinakin, said nine political parties would be participating in the elections. According to him, some of the parties that would be participating in the election include All Progressives Congress, Action Alliance, African Democratic Congress, and Social Democratic Party. He said, “We are fully prepared for the election and a total of 6,000 ad hoc staff will be recruited and trained for the poll. We have collaboration with the security agencies in the state as an adequate number of security men will be provided at the polling units. “A total of 18 political parties indicated interest to participate but nine have candidates and those nine will have their names on the ballot papers,” he added. However, the main opposition party in the state, the Peoples Democratic Party, announced its decision to boycott the elections alleging that the electoral management body would not be fair handed in dealing conducting the polls. Copyright PUNCH.
